Agilis’ Broker License Suspended by Norway’s FSA, DN Reports

-- B y   S t e p h e n   T r e l o a r
-- 
2011-03-31T06:59:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/agilis-broker-license-suspended-by-norway-s-fsa-dn-reports.html
Agilis Securities had its licenses
revoked by the Financial Supervisory Authority of Norway for
advising retail clients to engage in too frequent day-trading,
 Dagens Naeringsliv  reported, citing Eirik Bunaes, the agency’s
head of market supervision.  The breaches were uncovered during an inspection in June,
the Oslo-based newspaper reported. Agilis has issued a complaint
to the  Finance Ministry , according to Dagens Naeringsliv.  Bunaes confirmed the withdrawal to Bloomberg by telephone
today. Agilis' Chief Executive Officer Henrik Seland declined 
to immediately comment when contacted by telephone.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Treloar at 
 streloar1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
